      <h3>Like...</h3>
      <p>Like two stars,<br>
         They shine apart but share the same light.<br><br>
         Like a melody,<br>
         Different notes, but one song so right.<br><br>
         Like twin flames,<br>
         Dancing close, but still their own spark.<br><br>
         Like the ocean tide,<br>
         Always reaching for the moon in the dark.<br><br>
         Like you and I.<br>
         <em>Ezzie - 28th Friday February 2025</em></p>
    </div>

    <div class="poem-box">
      <h3>Just us</h3>
      <p>Love is in the quiet moments<br>
         in the way your words feel like home,<br>
         in laughter that lingers long after,<br>
         in the feeling that no one else could be you.<br><br>
         It’s not about distance or time,<br>
         just the fact that you’re mine and I’m yours.<br>
         Like a rhythm only we understand,<br>
         just there, just us.<br>
         <em>Ezzie - 9th Saturday February 2025</em></p>
    </div>

    <div class="poem-box">
      <h3>Ding!</h3>
      <p>The world felt quiet, dull, and wide.<br>
         Boredom creeping through my mind,<br>
         just noise and blur and aching space,<br>
         until your name lit up my face.<br><br>
         One ding, the screen lit up, and there you were.<br>
         A simple line, the softest stir,<br>
         and suddenly the sky turned blue!<br>
         The world made sense because of you.<br>
         <em>Ezzie - 25th Monday March 2025</em></p>
    </div>

    <div class="poem-box">
      <h3>The first</h3>
      <p>I said it like it's nothing.<br>
         I said it like it's everything.<br><br>
         Tossed it like a coin,<br>
         like maybe you'd step over it again.<br>
         But this time,<br>
         you picked it up.<br>
         Held it like it mattered.<br><br>
         You said it like it's nothing.<br>
         You said it like it's everything.<br><br>
         And suddenly,<br>
         I was everything too.<br>
         <em>Ezzie - 07 Monday April 2025</em></p>
    </div>
